{{Infobox company | name = Agriterra | logo = | caption = | type = [[Public limited company]] | traded_as = {{AIM|AGTA}} | fate = | predecessor = White Nile Limited | successor = | foundation = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = | location_country = [[Guernsey]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = [[Phil Edmonds]] (CEO) | industry = | products = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.agriterra-ltd.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }} '''Agriterra Limited''' (formerly: '''White Nile Limited''') is a [[Guernsey]]-registered agricultural investment company operating in Africa. The company is listed on the AIM [[London Stock Exchange]]. It is not to be confused with the agrarian development cooperation organisation Agriterra.<ref>[http://www.agriterra.org Agriterra]</ref>
White Nile Limited was established by [[Phil Edmonds]], a former England [[cricketer]]. The company started its operations in [[South Sudan]] as a [[petroleum]] company. It was partly owned by [[Nilepet]], a national oil company of South Sudan. In 2009, it changed its name and also its field of operations.<ref name=agriterra060109> {{Cite press release | title = EGM Statement | publisher = Agriterra | date =2009-01-09 | url = http://www.agriterra-ltd.com/News.aspx?ArticleId=2539886 | accessdate =2012-12-10}} </ref>
