[[file:Dioecesis Aegypti 400 AD.png|thumb|right|Map of the Diocese of Egypt in antiquity]]
The diocese of Ammonia ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Ammoniacensis|link=no}}) is a suppressed and [[titular see]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].<ref>''[[Annuario Pontificio]] 2013'' (Libreria Editrice Vaticana, 2013 {{ISBN|978-88-209-9070-1}}), "Sedi titolari", pp. 819-1013</ref> It is all that remains of the [[late antiquity|ancient]] [[bishopric]] that was centered the [[Siwa Oasis]] during [[late antiquity]],<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/t0118.htm Diocese of Ammoniace], at www.gcatholic.org
</ref> when it was in the [[Roman province]] of [[Marmarica]] and suffraged by the archdiocese of [[Darni]].  Today Ammoniace survives as a [[titular bishop]]ric and has been vacant since January 24, 1983.<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/d3a01.html David Cheney, Diocese of Ammoniace], at Catholic-Hierarchy.org. [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref>

