{{Infobox film | name =Hamu Beya - The Sand Fishers | image = | alt = | caption = | film name = | director =Andrey Samoute Diarra | producer = | writer = | screenplay = | story = | based on = | starring = | narrator = | music = | cinematography = | editing = | studio = | distributor = Icarus Films | released = 2014 | runtime =72 minutes | country =[[Mali]] | language = | budget = | gross = }} '''''Hamu Beya – The Sand Fishers''''' is a 2014 Malian documentary film about the [[Bozo people]] in [[Mali]] directed by Andrey Samoute Diarra.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://graphic.com.gh/entertainment/movies/23736-documentary-beya-hamu-the-sand-fishers.html| title=Documentary: Beya Hamu 'The Sand Fishers'| publisher=Ghana Graphic Online| date=27 May 2014| accessdate=2 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.icarusfilms.com/new2014/hamo.html| title=Hamou-Beya – The Sand Fishers| publisher=Icarus Films| accessdate=2 November 2015}}</ref> The film received the [[Africa Movie Academy Award for Best Documentary|Best Documentary]] award alongside ''[[Portrait of a Lone Farmer]]'' at the [[10th Africa Movie Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://dailypost.ng/2014/05/26/amaa-2014-clarion-chukwurah-patience-ozokwor-win-big-see-full-list-winners/| title=AMAA 2014: Clarion Chukwurah, Patience Ozokwor Win Big| work=Daily Post (Nigeria)| last=Orenuga| first=Adenike| date=26 May 2014| accessdate=2 November 2015}}</ref>
