The '''ITU Youth Forum''' is an initiative of the [[ITU-D]] Youth Program.<ref name="itusite">{{cite web|title=ITU TELECOM Youth Forums|url=http://www.itu.int/ITU-D/youth/itu__telecom_youth_forums.html|accessdate=5 April 2010|year=2010|publisher=International Telecommunication Union}}</ref> ITU-D is one of three sectors of the [[International Telecommunication Union]]. The forums bring together students from all over the world to discuss [[Information and communication technologies|Information technology]] and society-related topics.

The ITU Youth Forum is a recurring event arranged to be a part of either regional or global [[ITU Telecom World|ITU Telecom]] events. Forum participants (youth fellows) are typically from the ITU member states comprising the region in which the event is organised.{{citation needed|date=April 2010}} During the forum, youth fellows collaborate to produce joint declarations and/or action plans which are published by the ITU.<ref name="itusite"/>

