The '''Mayombe National Alliance''' ({{lang-pt|Aliança Nacional do Mayombe}}; '''ALLIAMA''') is a defunct, separatist organization that campaigned for the independence of [[Cabinda province]] from [[Portugal]]. ALLIAMA merged with the [[Action Committee of the Cabinda National Union]] and the [[Movement for the Liberation of the Enclave of Cabinda]] in 1963 to form the [[Front for the Liberation of the Enclave of Cabinda]] (FLEC). Cabinda is now a province and an [[exclave]] of [[Angola]].<ref name="a">{{cite book|last=Mullen|first=J. Atticus Ryan|author2=Christopher A. Mullen|year=1997|title=Unrepresented Nations & Peoples Organization, Yearbook 1997|pages=57}}</ref>
==See also== *[[1960s in Angola]] *[[Angolan War of Independence]] *[[Mayombe]]
